uk.ac.manchester.cs.mekon.owl.build

Class OBSectionBuilder

  • java.lang.Object
    • uk.ac.manchester.cs.mekon.owl.build.OBSectionBuilder
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    CSectionBuilder
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    OBOptimisingSectionBuilder

    public class OBSectionBuilder
extends java.lang.Object
implements CSectionBuilder
    Responsible for building a section of the Frames Model (FM) derived from a set of OWL ontologies via a standard "sanctioning" mechanism.

    The section-builder has an associated OModel over which the sanctioning will operate, and optionally a IReasoner object to be be attached to the generated CFrame objects to provide updating of their IFrame instantiations.

    The configuration for the sanctioning mechanism can be provided via the general MEKON configuration system, as can the configuration for the OModel over which the sanctioning will operate, and for a ORClassifier object (which is the default OWL-classification-based implementation of IReasoner) to be attached to all generated frames.

      • setAxiomPurgePolicy

        public void setAxiomPurgePolicy(OBAxiomPurgePolicy axiomPurgePolicy)
        Sets the axiom-purge policy, which determines which axioms, if any, will be removed from the OWL model after the section has been built and the reasoner loaded. Setting this attribute enables the minimisation of memory usage where appropriate. Defaults to OBAxiomPurgePolicy.RETAIN_ALL if method is never invoked.
        Parameters:
        axiomPurgePolicy - Required axiom-purge policy
